Being a Mom is a full-time job and requires a lot of energy to keep up with the kids. 
I am always looking at ways to maintain good health and stay fit.

While researching different ways to maintain an active life, I came to know that approximately 90% of women are deficient in Vitamin D. This is a concern that requires attention as this may lead to loss of bone density.

Apollo Clinic and Horlicks Women’s plus have partnered to offer a Vitamin D test worth Rs. 1500, FREE of cost along with a Free Doctor Consultation with each test at your nearest Apollo Clinic. 

This is a great initiative as after the age of 30 most women may face the risk of low bone density. 
Major issues related to poor bone health can be identified well in advance if you check your bone health from time to time.

I am going to take my free Vitamin D Test at Apollo Clinic and take the first step towards healthy bones. When are you going?

latestPosts.caption:
3 key lessons on how @mansiwadhwaofficial went from

Feeling Lost and following fitness fads 😩

To 👉🏼

Building Muscle and becoming Stronger, Healthier since the start of this year 💪🏼

When I met Mansi, she was struggling to navigate the ever so confusing and conflicting advice that social media has to offer

She had no structure to her training plan, and followed incorrect eating habits 📉😓

She faced the challenges before joining MSF:

1️⃣ Lack of Direction
- Not having a clear training plan and relying on just hearsay

2️⃣ Obsessing over Size
- Being stuck with the mindset of trying to get skinny

3️⃣ Harmful Habits:
- Smoking and alcohol were slowing her down, and she often deprived herself of food with phases of fasting

After joining MSF, Mansi has been able to take better control over fitness journey

She embraced the power of adding a scientific structure towards muscle building, proper nutrition and consistency

She stopped obsessing over set backs, and prioritised consistency

She was even able to quit smoking for good 🚀🔥

Mansi now receives compliments for her consistency and results, but she knows the real win is the direction and balance she has found in life 🌟💪

There are 3 fundamental lessons in how she got here:

✅ Consistency over Perfection
Not letting set backs become a reason for quitting the journey, but rather, showing up consistently.

✅ Quantified Nutrition is 🔑
Learning to eat to nourish your body and understanding your needs. No more starving for quick results; it’s now about fuelling her body for long term health

✅ Form over Weights 
Understanding that proper posture during workouts is a real game changer

While others here on Social Media may still be caught up with trying the latest fads, bullet proof coffees, and the likes of shilajits, Mansi grabbed this opportunity with both hands, trusted our MSF methods and transformed her life

Yours is waiting…

DM me “Action” to take action and start your journey to a healthier, stronger you before this year ends!

- MSF

latestPosts.caption:
It was my 42nd birthday yesterday and I am so grateful to have spent the past few days celebrating it in Jannat. 

“गर फिरदौस बर रूये जमी अस्त, हमी अस्तो हमी अस्तो हमी अस्त”

It was my third trip to Kashmir & each time it stumps me with its sheer beauty….but this time I also saw strength as the state survives turmoil and chaos, year after year and yet somehow manages to look pristine. 

Yes there were Jawans everywhere. 

Yes it was slightly unnerving. 

But yes it was peaceful too. Not crowded. The holiday felt like it. Unrushed and by all means it was luxurious. 

We stayed at the best properties, met some interesting people, we have come back with stories that will remain in our memories. 

Now on to my birthday, it feels more and more enriching. Calm, strength building up to face life with a smile rather than despair. The love I feel from people who I surround myself with, the pretences that have been dropped, the reality that has been accepted. It’s all feeling aligned.

Even on days that feel hazy, there is a sense of surety that this too shall pass. 

And for that I’m almost ecstatic to be growing old. And grateful , and so blessed 🙏🧿

If you are still here with me, you are truly my clan. Thank you. And I love you 🫶 
.
.
.
.
( Kashmir , heaven , vacation , Khyber , Gulmarg , birthday, philosophical, memoir)

latestPosts.caption:
MANSI WADHWA: Head of Content and Influencer Marketing, almost 42.

Thank you for these pics Priyanshu. I wanted to officially announce my new phase of life in a special way and you stepped in at the right moment. @lokeshvarun thank you for being a sport buddy! The pic is a decent representation of how we are 😂. 
I am turning another chapter this year and working full time has never been something I’d contemplated consciously but things change for a good reason and eGeonome is as good a reason as it gets. 

I drive 4 hours for work but it’s worth it ❤️. What an exciting new phase, great synergies and learnings uploading every single day. 

So much to learn from everyone I’ve chosen to surround myself with, it feels energising ✨. I miss working out for hours at the gym but hey, it’s just going to align eventually too. 
Always a fitness buff and never stopping 🧿. Tania is happy with my new job and the new routine is also settling in for her and my family. What I was scared to venture into once has now become my great joy 🤩 working in the field of healthcare ans AI, that has a ring to it now right ? 

Wish me luck and send good vibes 🆗 Upwards and onwards for the greater good 🤍

“Mom you are not going to be able to train like an athlete now coz you have a 9-5, so train like a normal person”
That’s profound gyan from my 17 yr old daughter. Funny how kids can just give some really good gyan ha .
6-7 pull ups. It’s not a big number but I’m happy to be pulling up, one week at a time 🙏I mean that’s the frequency of me attempting to get better at it given my current lifestyle and I’m quite happy with it. But yes it’s all upwards and onwards coz fitness is forever 🧿🙌
